Hydrogeophysical modelling

Coupled hydrogeophysical modelling example. This essentially represents the forward modelling step of the example presented in section 3.2 of the pyGIMLi paper.

### Parametros
## Espaciais
# Espaciais dos furos
bores = [-20, -15, -10, -5, 0, 5, 10, 15]                       # Posio central dos furos
prof_poco=-1.9
altura_poco= -0.1
raio_poco=0.95   #precisa ser decimal Ex:"3.00001"

# Espaciais do Terreno
box_esq=-30
box_dir=30
box_top=0.01
box_bottom=-20

# Espaciais discretizao de clulas
mesh_area=0.4               # area da mesh em metros^2
mesh_quality=30             # qualidade da mesh evitar valores acima de 33 por questes de performance

## Hidrulicos do meio
# Condutividade Hidrulica em m/s 
K_poco = 1e0       #poo
K_mundo1 = 1e-3    #latossolo
K_mundo2 = 5e-4     #fratura 
K_mundo3 = 1e-5    #rocha
#Marcador de regio do modelo
Mk_poco = 0       #poo
Mk_mundo1 = 1    #latossolo     
Mk_mundo2 = 2    #fratura 
Mk_mundo3 = 3    #rocha
L_mundo1 = -2   #profundade Layer mundo1
L_mundo2 = -10  #profundade Layer mundo2

# Resumir Condutividades hidrulicas em uma varivel s
kMap = [[Mk_mundo1, K_mundo1],  [Mk_poco, K_poco], [Mk_mundo2,K_mundo2],[Mk_mundo3,K_mundo3] ]   #Use [[RegionMarker, ConductivityValue], ...]

# Propriedades do meio poroso ADV
phi = 0.3                   # Porosidade meio
D = 0.01                    # Coeficiente de disperso m^2/s


## Traador                  # Condutividade eltrica da gua em S/m
sigma_a = -0.00031            
sigma_bx = 0.19330           # Termos da Eq. de Resistncia/concentrao = A+bx   
TracerCon = 13.27            # Concentrao em g/l
cementation_exponent = 1.1  # Exponente de cimentao para a resistividade do solo
res_water = 10000            # Resistividade da gua em Ohm.m


# Resistividade do meio em Ohm.m
Layer0=box_top
RLayer0=300
Layer1=-2                    # Prof. da camada 1
RLayer1=150                  # Resistividade da camada 1
Layer2=-8                    # Prof. da camada 2
RLayer2=4464                 # Resistividade da camada 2
Layer3=-24                   # Prof. da camada 3
RLayer3=3300                 # Resistividade da camada 4

# Configurao ERT 
ERT_dist= 600                # Distncia total dos eletrodos em m
ERT_elecs = 60               # Quantidade de eletrodos
ERT_spac = 10               # Espaamento entre os eletrodos em m
ERT_Array = 'dd'             # wn, ws, wa, wb, dd, pd, pp, grad 
nLayers=None

y_limit = 20                 # Set the Y-axis limit to cut off below DD12



# Temporais
TimeSimu_days = 2/24                     # Tempo de simulao em dias  
TimeSimu_sec = TimeSimu_days*24*60*60   # Tempo de simulao em seg  
TimeSimu_steps = 24                  # Quantidade de passos pra simulao
number_of_timesERT = 24        # Nmero de vezes que a simulao de ERT  executada


""" Clculos Espaciais relativos do furo """
esq = '.' + f'{raio_poco:.2f}'.split('.')[1]
dir = '.' + f'{1 - raio_poco:.2f}'.split('.')[1]#print(f'raio_poco={raio_poco:.2f} esq={esq} dir={dir}')

""" Clculo Espaamento dos eletrodos """
elecs = np.linspace(-ERT_dist/2, ERT_dist/2, ERT_elecs)


""" Clculo tempo de simulao """
t = pg.utils.grange(start=0.1, end=TimeSimu_sec,n=TimeSimu_steps)

t0 = pg.utils.grange(0,1000,n=TimeSimu_steps//2)
tn= pg.utils.grange(0,TimeSimu_sec,n=TimeSimu_sec/100)  #tempo grande pra estabilizar a simulao com Courrant Friederich s-Lewy (CFL)

# Criao da geometria de 3 camadas
world = mt.createWorld(start=[box_esq, box_top], end=[box_dir, box_bottom], WorldMarker=False, layers=[L_mundo1,L_mundo2]) 

# Create boreholes
poco = []
for pos in bores:
    poco.append(mt.createRectangle(start=[pos - raio_poco, altura_poco], end=[pos + raio_poco,prof_poco],marker=0)) #marker=42, isHole=True, boundaryMarker=12))
boreholes = poco[0]
for borehole in poco[1:]:
    boreholes = boreholes + borehole


# Create geometry of model
geom = world + boreholes

Condies de Fronteira

The problem further boundary conditions of the hydraulic potential. We use $p=p_0=0.75$ m on the left and $p=0$ on the right boundary of the modelling domain, equaling a hydraulic gradient of 1.75%.

\begin{split}c \frac{\partial u}{\partial t} & = \nabla\cdot(a \nabla u) + b u + f(\mathbf{r},t)~~|~~\Omega_{\text{Mesh}}\\ u & = h~~|~~\Gamma_{\text{Dirichlet}}\\ a\frac{\partial u}{\partial \mathbf{n}} & = g~~|~~\Gamma_{\text{Neumann}}\\ \alpha u + \beta\frac{\partial u}{\partial \mathbf{n}} & = \gamma~~|~~\Gamma_{\text{Robin}}\\ \frac{\partial u}{\partial \mathbf{n}} & = \alpha(u_0-u)~~|~~\Gamma_{\text{Robin}}\end{split}

https://www.pygimli.org/pygimliapi/_generated/pygimli.solver.html#pygimli.solver.solveFiniteElements

Fluid flow in a porous medium of slow non-viscous and non-frictional hydraulic

movement is governed by Darcy's Law according to:

\begin{align}\frac{K}{\mathbf{v}} + \nabla p & = 0 \\ \nabla \cdot \mathbf{v} & = 0\\ \text{leading}\,\,\text{to}\,\, \nabla\cdot(K \nabla p) & = 0 \quad \text{on} \quad\Omega\end{align}

We begin by defining isotropic values of hydraulic conductivity $K$ and mapping these to each mesh cell:

In[10]:
## Resoluo K  por Darcy e Potencial por Elementos Finitos
# Map conductivity value per region to each cell in the given mesh

mesh = mt.createMesh(geom, quality=mesh_quality, area=mesh_area, smooth=[1, 10])
K = pg.solver.parseMapToCellArray(kMap, mesh)

#pg.show(mesh, data=K, label='Hydraulic conductivity $K$ in m/s', cMin=1e-10, cMax=1e12, logScale=True, grid=True)

# Resoluo da discretizao do modelo de potencial hidrulico
#p = np.random.rand(mesh.cellCount())   # Teste aleatorio

# Resolver o modelo de potencial hidrulico
p = pg.solver.solveFiniteElements(mesh, a=K, bc=pBound, verbose=True)#stats=True)

# Atualizar a visualizao ou armazenar resultados
fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20, 20))
pg.show(mesh, data=K, label='Condutividade Hidrulica $K$ em m/s', cMap= 'viridis',logScale=True, ax=axs[0],orientation='horizontal')
pg.show(mesh, data=p, label='Potencial Hidrulico', cMin=np.min(p), cMax=np.max(p), ax=axs[1],orientation='horizontal')
plt.show()

Elementos Finitos Velocidade

We can now call the finite element solver with the generated mesh, hydraulic conductivity and the boundary condition. The sought hydraulic velocity distribution can then be calculated as the gradient field of $\mathbf{v}=-\nabla p$ and visualized using the generic pg.show() function.

In[11]:
# Resoluo da velocidade como o neg. do grad. do Pot. Hid.
vel = -pg.solver.grad(mesh, p) * np.asarray([K, K, K]).T #4D


fig, axs = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20,10))
pg.show(mesh, data=pg.abs(vel)/1e-2, cMin=np.min(vel), cMax=np.max(vel),
                label='Velocity $v$ in mm/s', ax=axs[1], cMap='YlGnBu', hold=True,showStats=True)
pg.show(mesh, data=vel, color='y', linewidth=0.6, dropTol=1e-12, ax=axs[1],
                hold=True)

pg.show(mesh, color='grey', linewidth=0.2, ax=axs[0],
                label='Malha de discretizao ',hold=True)

In[12]:
# Determinao da concentrao salina por cada clula do poo
Source_vector = pg.RVector(mesh.cellCount(),0) 

mm_stom_s=1e-3 
ltom3=1e-3
#prism=raio_poco*raio_poco
cil_ret=raio_poco*3.14/2
vol_extrd=cil_ret



""" tempos dif S= chuva seca """

for pos in bores:
    for y in np.linspace(prof_poco , altura_poco, num=100):
        sourceCelly = mesh.findCell([pos, y])
        if sourceCelly:
            if Source_vector[sourceCelly.id()]==0:
                Source_vector[sourceCelly.id()] = TracerCon*ltom3/ (sourceCelly.size()*vol_extrd)  # g/l *1e3 /m^3  #aproximao da concentrao salina do poo
            for x in np.linspace(pos-raio_poco,pos+raio_poco,num=100):
                sourceCellx = mesh.findCell([x, y])
                Source_vector[sourceCellx.id()] = TracerCon *ltom3/ (sourceCellx.size()*vol_extrd)  # g/m^3

ertScheme = ert.createData(elecs=elecs, schemeName=ERT_Array, spacing=ERT_spac)

meshERT = mt.createParaMesh(ertScheme, quality=mesh_quality, paraMaxCellSize=ERT_spac/4e1, nLayers=nLayers,
boundaryMaxCellSize=750, smooth=[1, 2])

pg.show(meshERT,label='Mesh de clculos ERT',figsize=(10,10),)

Lei de Archie

$$R_f = R_r (1 - S_w)^m$$ Rf is the fluid resistivity

Rr is the rock resistivity

Sf is the fluid saturation

m is the cementation exponent

In[]:
# Simulao eltrica por tempo, concentrao para condutividade pela Lei de Archie

timesERT = pg.IVector(np.floor(np.linspace(0, len(c) - 1, number_of_timesERT)).astype(int)) # Select 10 time frame to simulate ERT data

# Create conductivity of fluid for salt concentration :math:c
sigmaFluid = c[timesERT] * sigma_bx + sigma_a
c = np.array(c)  # Ensure c is a numpy array

# Calculate bulk resistivity based on Archie's Law, by ratio of res water and sigmaFluid
resBulk = petro.resistivityArchie(rFluid = res_water / sigmaFluid, porosity = phi, m=cementation_exponent, mesh=mesh, meshI=meshERT, fill=1)

# apply background resistivity model
rho0 = np.zeros(meshERT.cellCount())
resis = pg.Matrix(resBulk)
for cell in meshERT.cells():
    if cell.center()[1] < Layer3:
        rho0[cell.id()] = RLayer3
    elif cell.center()[1] < Layer2:
        rho0[cell.id()] = RLayer2
    elif cell.center()[1] < Layer1:
        rho0[cell.id()] = RLayer1
for i, rb in enumerate(resBulk):
    resis[i] = 1. / ((1. / rb) + 1. / rho0)
